  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The specific Young's modulus reduction per 1 wt% Al addition is stated as 2% in the abstract but 1.3% density reduction is also mentioned.",
    "Deformation mechanisms such as MBIP, DSBR, and SIP are introduced to describe plastic deformation in high SFe Fe-Mn-Al-C steels.",
    "The formation of intergranular kappa-star carbides is detrimental to ductility and toughness.",
    "Weldability and coatability are not well documented in the literature.",
    "The effective Al composition range for best mechanical properties in austenitic steels is narrow (7-10% Al).",
    "Industrial scale production remains a challenge due to high Al content processing issues like alumina formation."
  ]
